    <title>You might start seeing Instagram comments on Threads soon</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="An image showing the Threads logo" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RvCNAzKrpKqbTxFdkj_MR4Gd_7Q=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73587930/STK156_Instagram_threads_1.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Illustration: The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="GTzVrA"&gt;Instagram might roll out a way to share comments on other Instagram posts to Threads, according to Alessandro Paluzzi, who often reverse engineers Meta’s social media apps to find coming features.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="hUDe97"&gt;Paluzzi shared an image showing that when commenting on an Instagram post, there could be a new dropdown menu that lets users choose to share the comment only to Instagram or “also share on Threads.” &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id="tqczG0"&gt;
&lt;div class="iframely-embed"&gt;&lt;div class="iframely-responsive" style="padding-bottom: 100%;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.threads.net/@alex193a/post/C_8Xvn6OrP2" data-iframely-url="https://cdn.iframe.ly/api/iframe?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2F%40alex193a%2Fpost%2FC_8Xvn6OrP2%3Fxmt%3DAQGzcwLYmBssJ-WMH6o6-Z_j_eZdRqYWSVW8MUNLee2f2g&amp;amp;key=9ef4a209439e42bc59783ba959d50197"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="U4dPsI"&gt;Meta has made a few moves to integrate Threads with its other platforms in the past, such as showing Threads posts on Instagram or Facebook (and, later, &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/12/23957591/threads-facebook-instagram-suggested-posts-opt-out"&gt;letting users opt out&lt;/a&gt; of that). The Twitter-like short-posting social network also lacks DMs of its own, but users can still receive or send messages through Instagram. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="CMBmug"&gt;The bigger effort, of...&lt;/p&gt;
